headline: 4 Utility Stocks to Buy From the Thriving Electric Power Industry
summary: Expected rise in electric consumption, along with an increase in prices, bodes well for the prospect of the Utility-Electric Power industry. Top-ranked utilities like DUK, D, ETR and CNP are set to benefit from strong demand from their customer base.

headline: Is Duke Energy Fairly Priced After Clean Energy Investment News and a 15% Rally in 2025?
summary: Thinking about whether Duke Energy is a bargain or overpriced right now? Let's dig into what really matters for smart investors: value. Duke Energy's stock has delivered a strong 15.3% year-to-date return and is up 14.4% over the last year, although it saw a slight dip of 2.4% in the past week. Recent news about expanded investment in clean energy infrastructure and regulatory updates have kept Duke Energy in the spotlight. These developments are fueling both optimism around future growth...
